8.45am Hello everyone and welcome to our coverage of the second day from the Gabba. A hard-fought and very even opening to this series. So, that's it for the opening day of the Ashes. Who takes the honours? Mighty close to call. Not sure you can say. Mark Stoneman and James Vince did superbly before Australia struck back with three wickets - including the run out of Vince for 83 - but Dawid Malan and Moeen Ali did very well to see out the final hour. The pick of the bowlers was Nathan Lyon, some beautiful off spin, while Pat Cummins' pace picked up two important scalps. Andrew Miller is bashing out his match report which will be ready short, and we already have our first piece for you to digest as George Dobell assesses the importance of that second-wicket stand. It includes the phrase "hubristic baloney." We also have a gallery of the day
